SIMPLE: portentous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Portentous
<hw>Por*tent"ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>portentosus</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of the nature of a
portent; containing portents; foreshadowing, esp. foreshadowing ill;
ominous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For, I believe, they are <qex>portentous</qex> things.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Victories of strange and almost <qex>portentous</qex>
splendor.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence: Monstrous; prodigious; wonderful; dreadful;
<as>as, a beast of <ex>portentous</ex> size</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Roscommon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Por*tent"ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Por*tent"ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Porter</ent>⟦br⟧
